Paris Saint-Germain are reportedly planning to offer Paul Pogba a lucrative salary to join them on a free transfer this summer from Manchester United. Pogba’s future at Old Trafford remains unresolved with the Frenchman set to become a free agent at the end of the 2021/22 season. Reports earlier this season suggested the Red Devils have offered him a new mammoth £500k-a-week contract to stay at the club. Woman Kidnaps Five Children In Rivers AMAC Chairman-Elect Appeals To Buhari To Assent Amendment… However, the Daily Mail report that PSG are offering the player a ‘lucrative homecoming package’ in order to lure him to the Parc des Princes. Pogba is said to be happy to keep his options open until then, with remaining at Old Trafford not out of the question. But with United currently going through a huge slump in form and now outsiders for the Champions League, you wouldn’t bet against him departing at the end of the campaign. Rio Ferdinand discussed United’s current form on his Vibe with Five podcast and he addressed what Pogba and Bruno Fernandes need in the middle of the pitch. He said: “What I think Pogba needs and Bruno Fernandes needs… they need a Sergeant Major in that team that when they give it away or get a bit lax on the ball or when they’re out of position, a step short where they should be, they need someone in and around them screaming, drilling them. POLL “They haven’t got that player.” Pogba has made 215 appearances for United, scoring 39 goals. Back in October, he hinted that he could stay at United by insisting he ‘loves’ playing with ‘special’ Cristiano Ronaldo. When asked about his future Pogba, as quoted by Fabrizio Romano said: “I enjoy playing at Manchester United. “Then Cristiano is special – he’s one of the best in the world, I love playing with him.”